00:44:47,317 --> 00:44:50,309
Many of them
contracted smallpox.

872
00:44:50,387 --> 00:44:52,252
They met terrible fates,
many of them,

873
00:44:52,322 --> 00:44:54,347
but you can understand
why they opted for it.

874
00:44:54,425 --> 00:44:56,859
That gives you a measure
of what slavery was like,

875
00:44:56,927 --> 00:44:58,861
that people would take
that kind of risk.

876
00:45:01,398 --> 00:45:05,232
GATES: Harry Washington
was one of the lucky few.

877
00:45:05,302 --> 00:45:07,133
In the waning days of the war,

878
00:45:07,204 --> 00:45:08,933
the British put him on a ship

879
00:45:09,006 --> 00:45:10,837
and evacuated him to Canada.

880
00:45:12,076 --> 00:45:14,203
GORDON-REED: The British
definitely wanted to use

881
00:45:14,278 --> 00:45:18,146
the black to help them in their
struggle against the colonists,

882
00:45:18,215 --> 00:45:20,183
but they did not want to--

883
00:45:20,250 --> 00:45:22,184
had no intention of
actually making them,

884
00:45:22,252 --> 00:45:24,413
you know, equal to them

885
00:45:24,488 --> 00:45:25,580
and bringing them
and making them

886
00:45:25,656 --> 00:45:27,886
pan of British society, so,

887
00:45:27,958 --> 00:45:30,859
dropped them off there
and let them make their way.

888
00:45:33,163 --> 00:45:35,461
GATES: Harry didn't
stay long in Canada.

889
00:45:36,800 --> 00:45:38,529
He and his fellow
black loyalists

890
00:45:38,602 --> 00:45:43,904
were barred from voting
and exploited by local whites.

891
00:45:43,974 --> 00:45:46,966
So, when the British set up
a colony for former slaves

892
00:45:47,044 --> 00:45:49,035
back in Sierra Leone,

893
00:45:49,113 --> 00:45:51,513
Harry was among
the first to emigrate.

894
00:45:54,118 --> 00:45:55,983
He ended up near here,

895
00:45:56,053 --> 00:45:57,918
one of the very few slaves

896
00:45:57,988 --> 00:45:59,785
who ever made it back to Africa.

897
00:46:03,560 --> 00:46:06,222
Harry didn't necessarily
want to go back to Africa.

898
00:46:06,296 --> 00:46:09,265
You know what Harry wanted?
He wanted his old master

899
00:46:09,333 --> 00:46:11,733
George wanted-freedom.

900
00:46:11,802 --> 00:46:14,396
The right to do as he pleased.

901
00:46:14,471 --> 00:46:17,770
Unfortunately, he did not
find it here.

902
00:46:20,544 --> 00:46:22,808
The British government
in Sierra Leone

903
00:46:22,880 --> 00:46:26,816
tried to limit the property
rights of the black settlers.

904
00:46:26,884 --> 00:46:31,014
Harry fought back and was
banished for insubordination.

905
00:46:32,656 --> 00:46:34,783
After that, he disappeared.

906
00:46:36,827 --> 00:46:38,886
Harry was a rebel to the end,

907
00:46:38,962 --> 00:46:42,489
and it's probably best that
he turned his back on America,

908
00:46:42,566 --> 00:46:45,228
because he wouldn't have liked
what America became.

909
00:46:53,343 --> 00:46:56,710
The founding fathers built
a country committed to slavery.

910
00:46:58,048 --> 00:47:02,485
The site of Washington, DC
was chosen as our capital

911
00:47:02,553 --> 00:47:06,990
in order to appease southern
slave owners, and why not?

912
00:47:07,057 --> 00:47:10,584
They held an enormous
amount of power.

913
00:47:10,661 --> 00:47:12,822
CHRISTOPHER BROWN: None of it
exists without slavery.

914
00:47:12,896 --> 00:47:14,158
There are no settlements.

915
00:47:14,231 --> 00:47:16,392
There is no 13 colonies
without slavery.

916
00:47:16,466 --> 00:47:18,058
There is no United States
without slavery.

917
00:47:18,135 --> 00:47:21,002
There's no independence movement
