927
00:47:49,967 --> 00:47:53,027
And you see the statue of
the Native American on top?

928
00:47:53,103 --> 00:47:54,764
Symbol of freedom?

929
00:47:54,838 --> 00:47:57,739
One of the people who cast it
was a slave.

930
00:48:00,010 --> 00:48:03,309
But even if the ideals
of the American Revolution

931
00:48:03,380 --> 00:48:05,507
were perverted by slavery,

932
00:48:05,582 --> 00:48:08,710
the ideals themselves endured.

933
00:48:08,785 --> 00:48:11,618
They lingered in the hearts
of black people

934
00:48:11,688 --> 00:48:14,555
and they spread throughout
the Atlantic world.

935
00:48:20,898 --> 00:48:25,232
Saint-Domingue. At the close
of the American Revolution,

936
00:48:25,302 --> 00:48:27,031
this was a French colony.

937
00:48:28,839 --> 00:48:32,366
It was the world's largest
producer of coffee and sugar.

938
00:48:33,710 --> 00:48:36,543
And it had the largest
concentration of slaves

939
00:48:36,613 --> 00:48:39,047
in the Western Hemisphere.

940
00:48:39,116 --> 00:48:43,018
Almost twice as many Africans
